## Icons
Icons (`icon16.png`, `icon48.png`, `icon128.png`) are generated from the app's logo PNG using Pillow:
```bash
cd /path/to/project && source venv/bin/activate
python3 -c "
from PIL import Image
src = 'path/to/logo.png'
img = Image.open(src).convert('RGBA')
for size in [16, 48, 128]:
    img.resize((size, size), Image.LANCZOS).save(f'extension/icons/icon{size}.png')
"
```

## Popup Design
The popup (`popup.html` / `popup.css`) mirrors the main app's design system exactly:
- **Same CSS variables**: `--accent-gradient`, `--bg-primary/secondary/tertiary`, `--text-*`, `--border-color`, etc.
- **Same font**: `Outfit` from Google Fonts
- **Font Awesome 6** loaded from CDN (`cdnjs.cloudflare.com`) for all icons — no emoji
- **Header logo**: gradient rounded square (`logo-icon` div with `fas fa-rocket`) + "Apply**Pilot**" (Pilot in `var(--accent-primary)`)
- **No rounded outer corners** — Chrome's native popup window clips them; do not add `border-radius` to `html`/`body`/`.popup-container`

### Popup sections (authenticated view)
1. Header: gradient top bar + logo + status dot
2. **Inline notification bar** (`#popupNotification`) — hidden by default, slides in below the header on sign-in/sign-out/copy events
3. User card: gradient avatar with initials, name, email
4. Job detection row: briefcase icon + "Job detected on **{domain}**"
5. "Analyze This Job" gradient button (full width, bolt icon)
6. Hint text: "Extracts page content and sends it to AI for analysis"
7. Quick links grid (4 cols): Dashboard / Settings / Help / Logout
8. Footer: `v1.1.0`

### Inline notification bar — `#popupNotification`

Replaces the old `position: fixed` floating toast. The bar is always inside the popup frame and is never clipped by popup height changes during view transitions.

**Typography (source of truth: `extension/popup/popup.css`):** body text **14px**, **line-height ~1.45**, **max-height ~120px** with vertical scroll for long API messages (e.g. duplicate-job copy), **`align-items: flex-start`** so the icon aligns with wrapped lines; hint under the primary button (`.action-hint`) is **12px**. Do not shrink the bar back to a single-line **48px** clip — long `RES_3002` messages must remain readable.

```html
<!-- popup.html — inserted immediately after </header> -->
<div id="popupNotification" class="popup-notification hidden" role="alert" aria-live="polite"></div>
```

```css
/* popup.css — illustrative; match the live file */
.popup-notification {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 10px;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 1.45;
  max-height: 120px;
  overflow-x: hidden;
  overflow-y: auto;
  transition: max-height 0.25s ease, opacity 0.25s ease, padding 0.25s ease;
}
.popup-notification > span { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
.popup-notification.hidden { max-height: 0; padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; opacity: 0; }
.popup-notification.success { background: rgba(16,185,129,.18); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(16,185,129,.35); color: #34d399; }
.popup-notification.error   { background: rgba(239,68,68,.18);  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(239,68,68,.35);  color: #f87171; }
.popup-notification.info    { background: rgba(59,130,246,.18);  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.35);  color: #60a5fa; }
```

```javascript
// popup.js — showToast() targets the bar, not document.body
let _notifTimer = null;
function showToast(message, type = 'info') {
  const bar = document.getElementById('popupNotification');
  if (!bar) return;
  const icons = { success: 'fa-circle-check', error: 'fa-circle-xmark', info: 'fa-circle-info' };
  if (_notifTimer) { clearTimeout(_notifTimer); _notifTimer = null; }
  bar.className = `popup-notification ${type}`;
  const icon = icons[type] ?? icons.info;
  bar.innerHTML = `<i class="fas ${icon} notif-icon"></i><span>${message}</span>`;
  _notifTimer = setTimeout(() => { bar.classList.add('hidden'); _notifTimer = null; }, 3000);
}
```

**Never revert to `position: fixed` toast appended to `document.body`** — it disappears when the popup changes height during view transitions.

### Duplicate workflow start — `RES_3002`

If `POST .../workflow/start` returns **409** with `error_code === 'RES_3002'`, the user already has an application for that job. **`popup.js`** / **`service-worker.js`** must show an **info** (or warning-style) message via `showToast` / the same UX path — not a generic network error. Details: `applypilot-core.mdc` (`RES_3002`).

## Content extraction (`extractPageContent` in `popup.js`)

The popup injects **`extractPageContent`** via `chrome.scripting.executeScript` (not a static per-site selector list). Philosophy: clone a **single root**, strip chrome (scripts, nav, tracking attrs), then send text to the backend.

- **Default:** clone `document.body` (minus removed nodes), `innerText` → `job_text`.
- **Split-view job search UIs** (list column + detail pane): if the hostname matches **`\*.linkedin.(com|cn)`** and the path matches **`/jobs`**, prefer a **detail-pane root** so the first list row does not dominate the string:
  - Try `.jobs-search__job-details-body`, then `.jobs-details__main-content`.
  - Else prefer the wrapper around the largest `article.jobs-description__container`.
- If no root passes a minimum text-length check, fall back to **`document.body`**. Class names are **heuristic** — third-party DOMs change; keep fallbacks.

**Context menu** (`service-worker.js`): non-selection extraction uses the **same root-selection logic** as the popup; `h1` for notification title is taken from the **cloned root**, not `document.querySelector('h1')` first globally.

## Submitting to Backend

The extension POSTs `FormData` with only `job_text` — never `detected_title` or `detected_company`:

```javascript
const formData = new FormData();
formData.append('job_text', extractedText);
// Do NOT send detected_title / detected_company — page titles are unreliable
// (e.g. "(5) LinkedIn"). The dashboard shows skeleton shimmers while the
// Job Analyzer extracts the correct title and company from the job text.

const response = await fetch(`${CONFIG.API_BASE_URL}/workflow/start`, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${state.token}` },
    body: formData
});
```

### Backend: `detected_title` / `detected_company` Form params

`POST /api/v1/workflow/start` accepts two optional `Form` fields (retained for non-extension paths):

```python
detected_title_form:   Optional[str] = Form(None, alias="detected_title")
detected_company_form: Optional[str] = Form(None, alias="detected_company")
```

When omitted (the extension path), `job_title` and `company_name` are `null` at creation. The dashboard card shows skeleton shimmers (`status === 'processing'`, no title/company). The Job Analyzer agent populates both fields with AI-extracted values ~4 s into the workflow.

## Backend: InputMethod.EXTENSION
```python
# workflows/state_schema.py
class InputMethod(str, Enum):
    EXTENSION = "extension"  # from Chrome extension

# api/workflow.py
if source == "extension":
    input_method = InputMethod.EXTENSION.value
```

## Auth Endpoint for Extension
`GET /api/v1/auth/extension-status` — returns `{ "authenticated": bool, "user": {...} }`

## Landing Page Mockup
`ui/index.html` section `#extension` contains a `.popup-mockup` div that visually replicates the real popup UI for the landing page. CSS lives in `landing.css` under `/* ── Popup mockup ── */`. Keep it in sync with popup design changes.

## Non-Negotiables

1. **Never reference a popup DOM element without a null check** — elements may be absent if the HTML evolves. Example: `if (elements.copyBtn) elements.copyBtn.disabled = true;`. A missing element that is accessed unconditionally in `showExtracting()` or a similar setup function will throw a `TypeError` that silently aborts the entire extraction flow before the `try/catch` block is reached.
2. **Never send `detected_title` or `detected_company` from the extension** — browser page titles are unreliable (e.g. `"(5) LinkedIn"`, `"Careers | Company"`). Send only `job_text`; the dashboard shows skeleton shimmers while the Job Analyzer extracts the correct title and company.
3. **Never revert to `position: fixed` toast in the popup** — use the `#popupNotification` inline bar; see above.
4. **Handle `RES_3002` (409) from `/workflow/start` explicitly** — show the server message (or an equivalent friendly line) in the inline notification bar; do not treat it as an uncaught fetch failure.

